scspMIB.name: scspMIB
scspMIB.organization: IETF Internetworking Over NBMA Working Group (ion)
scspMIB.contactinfo: Jim Luciani (luciani@BayNetworks.com) Bay Networks Cliff X. Wang (cliff_wang@vnet.ibm.com) Colin Verrilli (verrilli@vnet.ibm.com) IBM Corp.
scspMIB.description: This module defines a portion of the management information base (MIB) for managing Server Cache Synchronization protocols entities.

ScspPIDType.name: ScspPIDType
ScspPIDType.description: The protocol type associated with a SCSP instance.

ScspHFSMStateType.name: ScspHFSMStateType
ScspHFSMStateType.description: The various states of the Hello Finite State Machine.

ScspCAFSMStateType.name: ScspCAFSMStateType
ScspCAFSMStateType.description: The various states of the Cache Alignment Finite State Machine.

SCSPVPIInteger.name: SCSPVPIInteger
SCSPVPIInteger.description: An integer large enough to contain the value of a VPI.

SCSPVCIInteger.name: SCSPVCIInteger
SCSPVCIInteger.description: An integer large enough to contain the value of a VCI.

scspServerGroupTable.name: scspServerGroupTable
scspServerGroupTable.description: The objects defined in this table are used to for the management of server groups. There is one entry in this table for each server group.

scspServerGroupEntry.name: scspServerGroupEntry
scspServerGroupEntry.description: Each entry contains attributes associated with a scsp server group.

scspServerGroupID.name: scspServerGroupID
scspServerGroupID.description: This is the Group ID of this SCSP server group instance.

scspServerGroupPID.name: scspServerGroupPID
scspServerGroupPID.description: This is the protocol ID of this SCSP server group instance.

scspServerGroupRowStatus.name: scspServerGroupRowStatus
scspServerGroupRowStatus.reference: RFC 1903, 'Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).'
scspServerGroupRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted from the scspServerGroupTable. This table is closely coupled with the scspLSTable, scspDCSTable, and the corresponding protocol dependent tables. A new row creation in this table results in creation of corresponding entries in the scspLSTable and scspDCSTable. In addition, entries in appropriate protocol dependent table may also be added. When the scspServerRowStatus is deleted by setting this object to destroy(6), this results in removing corresponding entries in scspLSTable, scspDCSTable, and those in corresponding protocol dependent table.

scspLSTable.name: scspLSTable
scspLSTable.description: The objects defined in this table are for the management of SCSP local server (LS).

scspLSEntry.name: scspLSEntry
scspLSEntry.description: Information about the Local Server in a SCSP group. Each entry contains attributes associated a LS.

scspLSID.name: scspLSID
scspLSID.description: This is the Local Server ID of this Local Server.

scspLSHelloInterval.name: scspLSHelloInterval
scspLSHelloInterval.description: This object contains the value for HelloInterval for the Local Server. It is the time (in seconds) between sending of consecutive Hello messages from this server.

scspLSDeadFactor.name: scspLSDeadFactor
scspLSDeadFactor.description: This object contains the value for DeadFactor. The DeadFactor along with HelloInterval are sent with outgoing 'Hello' messages. If the DCS does not received 'Hello' message from this LS within the time out interval 'HelloInterval*DeadFactor' (in seconds), then the DCS MUST consider the LS to be stalled.

scspLSCAReXmInterval.name: scspLSCAReXmInterval
scspLSCAReXmInterval.description: The time out interval (in seconds) for re-sending CA message to the DCS if no response is received.

scspLSCSUSReXmtInterval.name: scspLSCSUSReXmtInterval
scspLSCSUSReXmtInterval.description: The time out interval (in seconds) for re-sending CSUS Request to the DCS if not all CSA Records corresponding to the CSAS records in the CSUS message have been received.

scspLSCSUReXmtInterval.name: scspLSCSUReXmtInterval
scspLSCSUReXmtInterval.description: The time out interval (in seconds) for re-sending CSU Request to the DCS if not all CSA Records corresponding to the CSU request have not been acknowledged.

scspLSCSAMaxReXmt.name: scspLSCSAMaxReXmt
scspLSCSAMaxReXmt.description: The maximum number of retransmission of a CSA record. If acknowledge fails to occur when the maximum number is reached, an 'abnormal event' has happened between the LS/DCS link.

scspLSRowStatus.name: scspLSRowStatus
scspLSRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted from the scspLSTable. This table is closely coupled with DCS table and its corresponding protocol dependent tables. A new row creation in this table results in creation of new rows in the DCS table for each of its configured DCSs (peer servers). In addition, entries are created in the appropriate protocol dependent tables. When the scspServerRowStatus is deleted by setting this object to destroy(6), this results in removing the corresponding entries in the DCS table of the same Server Group. In addition, entries in the corresponding protocol dependent table will also be removed.

scspDCSTable.name: scspDCSTable
scspDCSTable.description: The objects defined in this table are used for the management of the DCS session between the LS and DCS.

scspDCSEntry.name: scspDCSEntry
scspDCSEntry.description: Information about each DCS session between the LS and its DCSs. The table is indexed by scspServerGroupID, scspServerGroupPID, and scspDCSID.

scspDCSID.name: scspDCSID
scspDCSID.description: This ID is used to identify a directly connected server(DCS).

scspDCSCAFSMState.name: scspDCSCAFSMState
scspDCSCAFSMState.description: The current state of the Cache Alignment Finite State Machine. The allowable states are: down(1), msNego(2), cacheSumm(3), cacheUpdate(4), aligned(5).

scspDCSCASequence.name: scspDCSCASequence
scspDCSCASequence.description: The current CA sequence number associated with this DCS.

scspDCSCAIn.name: scspDCSCAIn
scspDCSCAIn.description: The number of CA messages received from this DCS.

scspDCSCAOut.name: scspDCSCAOut
scspDCSCAOut.description: The number of CA messages sent to this DCS.

scspDCSCAInvalidIn.name: scspDCSCAInvalidIn
scspDCSCAInvalidIn.description: The number of invalid CA messages received from this DCS. During Master/Slave negotiation state, two types of messages are correct: 1) CA from the DCS has the M, I, and O bits on, with no CSAS records and sender's ID is larger than the LSID. 2) CA from the DCS has the M and I bits off and the sender's ID is smaller than the LSID. All other types of CA messages are invalid and ignored. During Cache Summarize State, two kinds of message errors are possible: 1) M bit in received CA is set incorrectly; 2) CA sequence number is neither equal nor one more than the current LS's CA sequence number when LS is slave or CA sequence number is neither equal nor one less than the current LS's CA sequence number when LS is master. Other common errors include failed check sum, failed authentication if applicable, errors in the message fields.

scspDCSCADuplicateIn.name: scspDCSCADuplicateIn
scspDCSCADuplicateIn.description: The number of duplicate CA messages received from this DCS. A CA message is considered duplicate when 1)LS is master and received a CA message with its sequence number one less than the current sequence number; or 2)LS is slave and received a CA message with its sequence number equal to the LS's current sequence number.

scspDCSMSState.name: scspDCSMSState
scspDCSMSState.description: The master/slave status of this DCS. This object should be ignored when CAFSM is in 'down' state.

scspDCSCSUSIn.name: scspDCSCSUSIn
scspDCSCSUSIn.description: The number of CSUS sent from this DCS to the LS.

scspDCSCSUSOut.name: scspDCSCSUSOut
scspDCSCSUSOut.description: The number of CSUS sent from LS to this DCS.

scspDCSCSUSInvalidIn.name: scspDCSCSUSInvalidIn
scspDCSCSUSInvalidIn.description: The number of Invalid CSUS sent from this DCS to the LS.

scspDCSCSURequestIn.name: scspDCSCSURequestIn
scspDCSCSURequestIn.description: The number of CSU requests LS received from this DCS.

scspDCSCSUReplyOut.name: scspDCSCSUReplyOut
scspDCSCSUReplyOut.description: The number of CSU replies sent from LS to this DCS.

scspDCSCSURequestOut.name: scspDCSCSURequestOut
scspDCSCSURequestOut.description: The number of CSU requests sent from LS to this DCS.

scspDCSCSUReplyIn.name: scspDCSCSUReplyIn
scspDCSCSUReplyIn.description: The number of CSU replies LS received from this DCS.

scspDCSCSUInvalidRequestIn.name: scspDCSCSUInvalidRequestIn
scspDCSCSUInvalidRequestIn.description: The number of invalid CSU requests LS received from this DCS. The possible errors in the CSU request messages: the received CSU request's Receiver ID is not equal to the LSID, etc. Other common errors include failed authentication if applicable, errors in the message fields, etc.

scspDCSCSUInvalidReplyIn.name: scspDCSCSUInvalidReplyIn
scspDCSCSUInvalidReplyIn.description: The number of invalid CSU replies LS received from this DCS. The possible errors in the CSU reply messages: the received CSU reply's Receiver ID is not equal to the LSID, etc. Other common errors include failed authentication if applicable, errors in the message fields, etc.

scspDCSCSAIn.name: scspDCSCSAIn
scspDCSCSAIn.description: The total number of CSA records received from this DCS to this LS.

scspDCSCSAOut.name: scspDCSCSAOut
scspDCSCSAOut.description: The total number of CSA records sent from LS to this DCS.

scspDCSCSAReXmted.name: scspDCSCSAReXmted
scspDCSCSAReXmted.description: The total number of CSA records re-transmited from LS to this DCS.

scspDCSCSAReXmtQDepth.name: scspDCSCSAReXmtQDepth
scspDCSCSAReXmtQDepth.description: The depth of CSA Re-transmit queue associated with this DCS. The CSAs in the Re-transmit queue are pending to acknowledged.

scspDCSRowStatus.name: scspDCSRowStatus
scspDCSRowStatus.reference: RFC 1903, 'Textual Conventions for version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv2).'
scspDCSRowStatus.description: This object allows DCS entries to be created and deleted from the scspDCSTable. This table is closely coupled with its corresponding protocol dependent table. A new row creation in this table results in creation of a new row in the corresponding protocol dependent table. When the scspServerRowStatus is deleted by setting this object to destroy(6), this results in removing the corresponding entries in its corresponding protocol dependent table.

scspCSAReXmExceed.name: scspCSAReXmExceed
scspCSAReXmExceed.description: Retransmission of a CSA to this DCS has exceeded maximum retry limit, indicating an 'abnormal event' has happened between the LS/DCS association. The HSFM associated with this DCS is transitioned into the 'Waiting' state, and a 'scspHFSMWaiting' trap is also generated.

scspCompliance.name: scspCompliance
scspCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that are required for the management of SCSP.

scspLSGroup.name: scspLSGroup
scspLSGroup.description: A collection of objects which support the management of the Server group and the Local Server. This group is mandatory.

scspDCSGroup.name: scspDCSGroup
scspDCSGroup.description: A collection of objects which support the management of the information exchange session between the LS and its associated DCS. This group is mandatory.
